## Full bleed layout

Your blog posts should have a maximum width of between 60ch - 75ch to make them readable by the human eye ğŸ‘â€ğŸ—¨

> [x]ch = x "0"s in the font you are using

So we place our content in a grid that looks like this post.

We also can account for small gutters to the side so the text isn't too close on mobile.

Anytime we want to take up the whole space, we add a class which spans the whole grid.
We can also use some negative margin to span the gutters too! (Nice for hero images)

```
article {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr min(70ch, 100%) 1fr;
  padding: 32px var(--gutter-width);

  & > * {
    grid-column: 2;
  }

  & > .full-ğŸ©¸ {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
  }

  & > .full-ğŸ©¸-gutter {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    margin-left: calc(var(--gutter-width) * -1);
    margin-right: calc(var(--gutter-width) * -1);
  }
}
```

